extends pug/layout.pug

block head
  title locize - how it works

block content
  
  section.section-tertiary.features.text-center
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12.text-center
          .section-heading
            h2 For Traditionalists
            p.head
              | Use locize like your traditional desktop based translation tool (just better).
            hr
      .row
        .col-md-12
          .container-fluid
            .row
              .col-md-6
                .feature-item
                  .device-container(style="margin: 0 auto 0;")
                    .device-mockup.macbook_2015.silver
                      .device
                        .screen
                          img.img-responsive(src='img/screenshots/screen/mt_s.jpg', alt='locize editor')
              .col-md-6
                .feature-item
                  h3 Manual Import / Export
                  p Use locize by importing and exporting the translation files.
                  p Take advantage from the smart translation memory and machine translations.
                  p 
                    | Learn more about the 
                    a(href="https://docs.locize.com/supported-formats.html" target="_blank") supported formats.

  
      .row
        .col-lg-12.text-center
          .section-heading
            h2 For Automators
            p.head
              | Automating parts of the process.
            hr
              
      .row
        .col-md-12
          .container-fluid
            .row
              .col-md-6
                .feature-item
                  h3 Powerful API / Sync tool
                  p 
                    | You can control your localization project by using our full fledged 
                    a(href="https://docs.locize.com/api.html" target="_blank") API.
                  p 
                    | Want to sync with your local code repository or during build time. All possible using our 
                    a(href="https://github.com/locize/locize-cli#synchronize-locize-with-your-repository-or-any-other-local-directory" target="_blank") Sync tool.

              .col-md-6
                .feature-item
                  .device-container(style="margin: 0 auto 0;")
                    .device-mockup.macbook_2015.silver
                      .device
                        .screen
                          img.img-responsive(src='img/screenshots/screen/cli_s.jpg', alt='locize cli')

              
      .row
        .col-lg-12.text-center
          .section-heading
            h2 For Innovators
            p.head
              | Being more efficient using locize.
            hr
              
      .row
        .col-md-12
          .container-fluid
            .row
              .col-md-6
                .feature-item
                  .device-container(style="margin: 0 auto 0;")
                    .device-mockup.macbook_2015.silver
                      .device
                        .screen
                          img.img-responsive(src='img/screenshots/screen/incontext_editor_s.jpg', alt='locize incontext')
              .col-md-6
                .feature-item
                  h3 The next level of localization
                  p Directly connect your project with locize.
                  ul 
                    li Automatically get new untranslated segments sent to locize.
                    li Directly consume translations from our CDN.
                    li Directly translate in the context of you web application.
                  p 
                    | See the full power in this 
                    a(href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9NOzJhgmyQE" target="_blank") video sample 
                    | for react.js. Learn more about the integration options using i18next or other i18n frameworks below.

                  

  
  section.section-white
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12.text-center
          .section-heading
            h2 There is an integration option for everyone
            p.text-muted Locize offers a big variety of integrations options.
            hr

  section.section-gray(style="padding: 0;")
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-4(style="position: relative;")
          .integration(style="height: 840px; background-color: #fff; border: solid 1px #ccc; position: relative; top: -100px; width: 100%; border-radius: 4px;")
            .integration-name.text-center 
              img(src="/img/howto/locizify.svg" style="height: 40px")
            .text-center.text-muted Zero effort - drop one line of code.
            .text-center 
              img(src="/img/howto/locizify-frameworks.png" style="width: 80%; margin: 10px 0 0;")
            .integration-features
              | Where to use:
              ul
                li Optimal for websites
                li Suitable for non developers, too
                li Minimal overhead to instrument your code
                li Flexible translations options like, plurals, interpolation, url fragments
                li Based on our virtualdom implementation on top of i18next
                li Optimal for Wordpress, Shopify and other site generators
            .integration-start
              a.btn.btn-outline.btn-xl(href='https://docs.locize.com/instrumenting-your-code.html#locizify', target='_blank', style="background-color: #ccc") Learn more!
        
                
        .col-md-4(style="position: relative;")
          .integration(style="height: 840px; background-color: #fff; border: solid 1px #ccc; position: relative; top: -100px; width: 100%; border-radius: 4px;")
            .integration-name.text-center
              img(src="/img/howto/i18next.svg" style="height: 40px")
            .text-center.text-muted Best translation management for i18next.
            .text-center 
              img(src="/img/howto/i18next-frameworks.png" style="width: 80%; margin: 10px 0 0;")
            .integration-features
              | Where to use:
              ul
                li Suitable for all UI Frameworks, reactjs, angular, vue, backbone, ember, ...
                li Minimal programming skills required
                li Flexible translations options like, plurals, interpolation, context, ...
                li Based on open source i18n framework i18next
                li Usable on web, mobile and desktop and server
            .integration-start
              a.btn.btn-outline.btn-xl(href='https://docs.locize.com/instrumenting-your-code.html#i18next', target='_blank', style="background-color: #ccc") Learn more!
        

        .col-md-4(style="position: relative;")
          .integration(style="height: 840px; background-color: #fff; border: solid 1px #ccc; position: relative; top: -100px; width: 100%; border-radius: 4px;")
            .integration-name.text-center other options
            .text-center.text-muted(style="margin-top: 12px;") File based solution.
            .text-center
              i.fa.fa-files-o(style="font-size: 60px; margin: 36px 0 54px;")
            .integration-features
              | Where to use:
              ul
                li Using with frameworks like react-intl, vue-i18n, i18n.js, angular-i18n, jquery-i18n, ...
                li We provide you with a script to simplify loading translations to your javascript client,...
                li Optimal for solutions based on formats like xliff, mo, po, android xml, ...
                li Using our API you can build anything you could think of
            .integration-start
              a.btn.btn-outline.btn-xl(href='https://docs.locize.com/instrumenting-your-code.html#other-options', target='_blank', style="background-color: #ccc") Learn more!


  section.section-primary
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12.text-center
          .section-heading
            h2 Continuous Localization Lifecycle
            p.text-center Our goal is to provide you with a complete set of features to enable a continuous localization process.
            hr
              
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          
          h3 Save missing: Automatical adding of new text content
          
          p.light-font For both locizify and i18next you can enable the save missing feature. Once enabled new content will automatically added to your localization project.
          
          h3 Locize CDN: Publishing translation
          
          p.light-font If not turned off translations will automatically published to our CDN. No need to download translations or redeploying of your app for changes to take effect.
          
          h3 API / CLI client
          
          p.light-font Use our API or CLI client to automate your process - if you prefer not depending on our CDN.
          
          h3 Versioning
          
          p.light-font Like on your repository you can add multiple versions to your project at no extra cost - work on latest while developing and pull the latest translations to your production version when ready to deploy a new version of your application.

        
                
